{
  "market_read": "Markets opened stronger than feared despite pre-market caution — broad-based rally with VIX down 2.9%, advance-decline 1.85:1, and all sectors green except Energy. US-Iran peace talks progress is the dominant positive catalyst, pulling crude lower and supporting risk appetite. Key watchpoints: LT miss (-4.3%) weighing on construction/capex theme, while M&M beat (+6.3%) is lifting Auto broadly; COFORGE +9.6% post-results is an IT mid-cap bright spot. Crude/rupee risk has eased marginally (Brent below $110, rupee 24p stronger at 95.04) but geopolitical tail remains live.",
  "watchlist": [
    {
      "symbol": "PNBHOUSING",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Currently held at +7.6% unrealized gain. Need fresh data to assess whether to trail SL, partially book, or hold toward target. PSU Bank cluster strong today (+1.63%) which may support housing finance."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "GOLDBEES",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Currently held at -1.1%. Gold/silver surging on MCX (gold +1.7%, silver +3.1%) on weaker dollar and US-Iran peace optimism. Need to reassess whether thesis is intact or if gold rally is fading."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "ADANIPORTS",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Currently held at +2.1%. Ports sector benefits from trade volumes; need to check if Strait of Hormuz tension easing improves shipping route sentiment. Trail SL assessment needed."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "BANDHANBNK",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Currently held at -0.4%. Banking sector up +1% today. Need to check if position has recovered or deteriorated since entry. Evaluate hold vs exit."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "HAL",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Currently held at +1.7%. Defence sector; geopolitical tensions (US-Iran, India macro) keep defence in focus. Assess whether to trail SL given modest gains."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "COFORGE",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Q4 results drove +9.6% gap-up today — one of the sharpest post-result moves in IT mid-cap. Already on watchlist. Evaluate if momentum continuation entry is viable after the gap or if overshoot risk is high."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "M&M",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Q4 PAT +48.5%, SUV/tractor demand strong, stock up 6.3% — top Nifty 50 gainer. Auto sector leads today (+1.59%). Need full data to assess if entry makes sense post-gap or if it's extended."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "CAMS",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Gapped up 10.6% on Q4 results beat. Financial services sector leader today. CAMS benefits from strong SIP/MF industry AUM growth. Assess if post-gap momentum entry has merit."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "AUROPHARMA",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Pharma sector up +0.89%, AUROPHARMA +5.1% near 52-week high territory. Pharma is defensive amid macro uncertainty. Bullish RSI signals flagged in pre-market research. Evaluate swing entry."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "BIOCON",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "RSI trending up scan flagged it; +5.66% today. Biosimilars/pharma defensive play. Succession buzz may be adding speculative interest though promoter denied imminence. Evaluate setup quality."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "MARICO",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Within 1% of 52-week high; FMCG sector rallying on rural demand recovery narrative (+4.68% today). Defensive quality name with margin recovery thesis. Check if breakout above 52w high is confirmed."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "VEDL",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Metal sector strong (+0.82%), VEDL up 6.3% on 3.3x volume. Aluminium jumping on ceasefire optimism. Near 52-week high. High volume surge makes this a candidate for momentum entry or MIS."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "TITAGARH",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Capital Goods sector leader today +9.5%, gapped up 10.5%. Railway/wagon capex theme. Though LT miss is a headwind for broader capex, TITAGARH operates in a different sub-segment. Evaluate post-gap setup."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "RRKABEL",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Volume surge 8.2x with +0.84% — institutional accumulation signal despite muted price move. Cables/wires capex theme; POLYCAB Q4 results today may provide read-through. Check for breakout setup."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "IRCON",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Construction sector positive with IRCON +3.39%. Railway/infra execution story; despite LT miss weighing on broader construction, IRCON is government railway contractor with different dynamics. Assess setup."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "GABRIEL",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Auto components +3.54% on 3x volume — strong signal tied to M&M beat and Auto sector leadership. GABRIEL makes ride-control products for 2W/4W/CVs. Evaluate CNC swing setup on Auto sector strength."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "LALPATHLAB",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Extraordinary volume surge 11.4x with only +0.18% price change — classic institutional accumulation or large block trade. Diagnostics/healthcare defensive. Need full data to understand the volume anomaly."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "HFCL",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Telecom sector leader +6.24% on 3.1x volume, near 52-week high (-4.2% from high). Telecom infra/fibre play with active momentum. KM Birla returning to Vodafone Idea adds telecom sector sentiment. Evaluate."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "ABCAPITAL",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Financial services +6.94% on 2.4x volume. Aditya Birla Capital recommended by analysts in pre-market. Financial services sector showing broad strength. Evaluate swing setup."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "PSUBNKBEES",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "PSU Bank sector strongest sector today +1.63%. PNB up 4% on Q4 beat; MAHABANK +5.71%. ETF gives diversified exposure without single-bank risk. Portfolio already light on financials after prior exits."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "CHOLAHLDNG",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Volume surge 4.8x with +3.43%. Chola Holdings is a financial services holding company. Strong volume signal warrants full data check."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "COALINDIA",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Energy sector on watchlist; crude falling benefits India macro but coal remains domestic energy anchor. Need to assess current setup and whether the thesis has evolved since last check."
    },
    {
      "symbol": "POLYCAB",
      "exchange": "NSE",
      "reason": "Q4 results due today — key capex/cables bellwether. Results will set direction; if beat, could drive strong momentum. RRKABEL volume surge 8.2x may be anticipatory positioning. Need data post-result."
    }
  ],
  "drop_from_watchlist": ["NAVINFLUOR", "SUMICHEM", "FINCABLES", "SOBHA", "BHEL", "NIFTYBEES", "DABUR"],
  "drop_reasons": "NAVINFLUOR and SUMICHEM were chemical sector plays — SUMICHEM already +9.5% today making entry risky at extended levels, NAVINFLUOR has no fresh catalyst today. FINCABLES drops in favour of RRKABEL which has the stronger volume signal. SOBHA drops as GODREJPROP is down 3.9% suggesting realty-specific stress rather than sector-wide strength. BHEL is flat with volume surge already absorbed. NIFTYBEES replaced focus by sector-specific ETF (PSUBNKBEES) which has cleaner momentum today. DABUR dropped for now as MARICO has the stronger 52-week high proximity signal — monitoring both is redundant."
}
